<ul><li>Happy the people whose annals are tiresome.
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Thomas_Carlyle" title="Thomas Carlyle">Thomas Carlyle</a>, <i>The French Revolution, A History</i> (1837), Part I, Book II, Chapter I.</li></ul></li></ul>
<ul><li>No great man lives in vain. The history of the world is but the biography of great men.
